article.headline: Texas College 69, Grambling State 67
article.story: GRAMBLING, La. (AP) -- Andre' Ratliff hit a jumper with seven seconds left in the game to lift Grambling State to 69-67 win over Texas College on Tuesday night. Ratliff also scored 27 points, hitting 10-of-18 shots, and had three assists for Grambling (1-0). Anthony Williams added 9 points and George Akpele 8 for the Tigers. On its last possession, Texas College (1-2) lost the ball on a turnover by Mike Dale, the team's top scorer with 27 points. Dale also brought in 13 rebounds and had 7 assists. For the game, Grambling hit 23-of-63 shots (36.5 percent) and made 7-of-16 3-pointers. The Steers made 24-of-54 shots (44.4 percent) and hit 5-of-14 3-pointers. Texas College led in rebounds, 43-42, but had more turnovers, 16-13. The Steers led 36-30 at the halftime.
